y happened.\n\nThe Supreme Court ruled today that IEEPA \u2014 a 1977 emergency law \u2014 can\u2019t be used to impose sweeping global tariffs without Congressional authorization. Roberts wrote it. Thomas, Alito, and Kavanaugh", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 5822}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASFqpq7kd", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 106, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "hat", "id": 8434317, "raw_content": "Section 301 of the Trade Act of 1974\n\n- Allows tariffs and trade restrictions to address unfair trade practices.\n\n- Used historically to impose tariffs on China.\n\n- Requires an investigation and (at least in theory) consultations with the targeted country.\n\nSection 232 of the Trade Expansion Act of 1962\n\n- Allows tariffs for national security reasons.\n\n- Trump already used this for steel/aluminum tariffs.\n\n- Still valid independently of IEEPA.\n\n Section 122 of the Trade Act of 1974\n\n- Can impose temporary tariffs (up to ~15%) for \u201cbalance-of-payments\u201d reasons.\n\n- Time-limited (e.g., 150 days without extension) and more constrained than IEEPA.\n\nThese authorities are narrower in scope, typically require formal procedures or findings, and (in some cases) are more time-limited than the broad emergency tariffs under IEEPA.", "author": "sleepy_bob_ross", "created": 1771602826979, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "ActualStory", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Trump can still impose Tariffs regardless of the SCOTUS ruling, here's how.", "last_comment_created": 1771633201029, "content": "<p>Section 301 of the Trade Act of 1974</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Allows tariffs and trade restrictions to address unfair trade practices.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Used historically to impose tariffs on China.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Requires an investigation and (at least in theory) consultations with the targeted country.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Section 232 of the Trade Expansion Act of 1962</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Allows tariffs for national security reasons.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Trump already used this for steel/aluminum tariffs.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Still valid independently of IEEPA.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Section 122 of the Trade Act of 1974</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Can impose temporary tariffs (up to ~15%) for \u201cbalance-of-payments\u201d reasons.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Time-limited (e.g., 150 days without extension) and more constrained than IEEPA.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These authorities are narrower in scope, typically require formal procedures or findings, and (in some cases) are more time-limited than the broad emergency tariffs under IEEPA.</p>\n", "score_down": 2, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 15, "score_up": 108, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "SAVE AMERICA", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2024919278550429792", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASFqprVC5", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 55, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8434841, "raw_content": "", "author": "KuzoKevin", "created": 1771615635485, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASFqprVC5.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/saras76/status/2024919278550429792", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "\"No. Please. I'm NOT talking to you! I don't talk to CNN! It's FAKE NEWS!!\" ", "last_comment_created": 1771615635485, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 0, "score_up": 55, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 8, "created": 1771613351000, "id": "2024919278550429792", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/amplify_video_thumb/2024918050638557185/img/Ooh5FJPAH-dToe59.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2024918050638557185/pl/wUtZ7I-7Q90D8lmp.m3u8", "aspectRatio": [16, 9], "heightRatio": 56, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2024918050638557185/vid/avc1/480x270/B8LLZ_zbCZbl5vWm.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2004790405431238656/GvZ-Rhge_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Sara Rose \ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83c\udf39", "username": "saras76"}, "content": "TRUMP: \"No. Please. I'm NOT talking to you! I don't talk to CNN! It's FAKE NEWS!!\" \ud83d\udd25 \ud83e\udd23", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 247}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2024910238219211231", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASFqprVKP", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 53, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8434865, "raw_content": "", "author": "CyanScales", "created": 1771616367006, "profile_picture": "1cOg4Zdci1jH", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Michalusmichalus", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASFqprVKP.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/BasedMikeLee/status/2024910238219211231", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "While IEEPA is absurdly vague in countless ways, it expressly authorizes the President to \u201cregulate \u2026 importation.\u201d . . . Congress has grown addicted to the practice of adopting impossibly vague statutory language, effectively delegating its lawmaking power to the other two branches. ", "last_comment_created": 1771616786188, "content": "", "score_down": 1, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 1, "score_up": 54, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 0, "created": 1771607594000, "id": "2024895129765442015", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1213023547/Twitter_2_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Senator Ron Johnson", "username": "SenRonJohnson"}, "content": "The tariff case cried out for a unanimous decision. However, both sides made reasonable arguments leading to a split decision. In the end, SCOTUS decided nothing and created a HUGE mess. \n\nBut the underlying mess is created by sloppy congressional language in bills that are not", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 3051}, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 143, "created": 1771611196000, "id": "2024910238219211231", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1888964527821139968/A047e0lQ_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Mike Lee", "username": "BasedMikeLee"}, "content": "While IEEPA is absurdly vague in countless ways, it expressly authorizes the President to \u201cregulate \u2026 importation.\u201d\n\nGiven that tariffs are the principal means by which the U.S. government \u201cregulate[s] \u2026 importation,\u201d I find it puzzling that the Supreme Court believes IEEPA", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 1549}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}], "status": true}